From c918bf060bed8c04ce24b2df1ad5099b9c5532bb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: operations-jacrentals <operations@jacrentals.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 21:53:24 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] Make the customer pulses mean something again (B7, B8)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Two flag pulses fired on the wrong condition. Both matched their own spec
comments, so these are approved behaviour changes (Jac, 2026-07-18), not
typo fixes — the comments are updated alongside the code.

B7 — 'New Customer' no longer pulses.
  payBad was `!/^(Paid|Current)$/`, and 'New Customer' is the value EVERY
  customer is created with that nothing in the client ever advances. So every
  brand-new zero-balance signup alarmed exactly like someone genuinely Unpaid
  — the largest single source of pulse-noise on the card. Added to the quiet
  set. Deliberately kept as a NEGATIVE test so any unrecognised or legacy
  payStatus still pulses instead of going silently quiet; 'Paid' stays in the
  pattern for the same reason (live data is known to carry off-vocabulary
  values — see "Don't Contact" on the funnel fields).

B8 — 'Payment Due' now pulses and 'No Billing' goes steady, swapping them.
  Previously a member who was never enrolled (nothing actually late) flashed,
  while a member whose membership invoice was genuinely overdue and unpaid sat
  calm. Both stay red and both stay surfaced; only which one earns the motion
  cue changes. Rationale: the counter chases money that is late; a missing
  enrolment is a back-office fix.

Visible change: fewer pulsing pills on the Customers list (no more New
Customer), and an overdue member now draws the eye instead of an unenrolled
one.

Gates on this branch: smoke, logic-test, lease-test, lease-deploy-test,
promote-test, deck-test, cachebust-test, gen-rule-usage --check,
check-window-catalog, check-design-md, gen-code-map --check — green.
check-cachebust is RED and expected to be: app.js changed vs trunk and the
shared ?v= token is bumped by tools/bump-cachebust.mjs at /merge time, not on
the feature branch. Same is true of the sibling audit branches.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
